The Herald Senior Arts Reporter All is set for the Castle Tankard to be held at the Borrowdale Racecourse, Harare, tomorrow. The event will see Zimdancehall musicians Enzo Ishall and Winky D sharing the stage with sungura maestro Alick Macheso. The horse racewill run under the theme “Our Race, Our Beer. Our Legacy.” In an interview, Delta corporate affairs manager Patricia Murambinda said everything was going according to plan for hosting the event. “We have been sponsoring the race since 1962 hence this year’s theme — Our Race, Our Beer, Our Legacy,” she said. Murambinda said the programme had already been lined-up. “On Saturday, we will have the races starting at 12.10pm with the final race being the Group 1 race, Castle Tankard running at 3:50pm,” she said. “We will also have a consumer activation Dash for Cash where 10 lucky consumers will race against each other. “There will be two races separate for men and women. The winners will stand a chance to win various cash prizes which include, US$100, US$75 and US$50 instantly.” Murambinda said apart from racing, there was also entertainment by local artistes. “MC Elroy and DJ Sammy Benz will start us off at 10.30am,” she said. “Other disc jockeys include DJ Naida and Judgement Yard will also play during the after party. “The highlight of the event is the after party show which will feature seasoned musicians such as Enzo Ishall, Aleck Macheso and Winky D who will be live on stage.”